      "text": "Theta (UK:  THEE-tə, US:  THAY-tə, uppercase Θ or ϴ; lowercase θ; cursive ϑ; Ancient Greek: θῆτα thē̂ta Greek pronunciation: [tʰɛ̂ːta]; Modern: θήτα thī́ta Greek pronunciation: [θita]) is the eighth letter of the Greek alphabet, derived from the Phoenician letter Teth 𐤈. In the system of Greek numerals, it has a value of 9.",
